Description. Male ( 9.5 mm , holotype ). Head .
Antenna 1
(
Fig. 2
): 55–60 % length of body, about 25 % longer than antenna 2 ; peduncular articles 1–3 have a length ratio of 1 : 0.70 : 0.35 ; primary flagellum with 23 articles, almost all flagellar articles bearing lanceolate aesthetascs accompanied by setae; accessory flagellum 3 –articulate, terminal article small, bearing 3 simple setae.
Antenna 2
(
Fig. 3
): gland cone acute without setae; peduncular article 4 as long as article 5 , both articles setose with short stiff setae; flagellum non flattened with 11 + 1 articles, calceoli present. Mandibles subequal: left mandible (
Fig. 6
) with incisor 5 –dentate, lacinia mobilis 5 –dentate, setal row with 5 serrate setae, triturative molar with plumose seta; palp article 2 (
Fig. 8
) 0.25 × longer than article 3 with 3 long and 9 short setae, article 3 bearing 4 A-setae, 4 B-setae, 22 D-setae and 5 E-setae; incisor of right mandible (
Fig. 7
) 5 –dentate, lacinia mobilis bifurcate, setal row with 5 serrate setae.
Maxilla 1
, right (
Fig. 12
): inner plate with 12 plumose setae, outer plate with 11 pectinate robust setae; right palp massive, palp articles 1–2 have a length ratio of 0.25 : 1 , article 2 bearing 4 strong pointed peg setae, 1 serrate and 1 plumose setae on apex; left palp feeble (
Fig. 13
), articles 1–2 have a length ratio of 0.25 : 1 , article 2 bearing 5 short strong and 3 stiff setae on apex.
Maxilla 2
(
Fig. 11
): inner plate with oblique row of 8–10 plumose setae on inner margin; outer plate slightly broader than inner plate with 4 stiff serrate and 8–12 slender setae on apex. Upper lip (
Fig. 10
): subrhomboid, with minute setae at apex. Lower lip (
Fig. 9
): inner lobes absent. Maxilliped (
Fig. 14
): peduncle trapeziform with sets of long setae on inner face; inner plate (
Fig. 16
) with 3 simple strong peg setae on apex and with 1 same setae sub-apically, 5 long simple setae on apex and 14 plumose setae extending from inner margin to apex; outer plate (
Fig. 15
) with a row of 10 medial robust serrate setae and with parallel row of 16 small stiff setae, 5 plumose setae on apex; palp four articulate, article 2 weak with 2 serrate setae at outer margin.
